  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>\"I can see the future.\"</em></p><h5 id=\"benefit\">Benefit</h5><p>As a fortune teller you are able to determine whether someone's future is bright or not. A number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per long rest, you can tell someone's fortune as a bonus action. When you would do so, you roll a 1d4. If the result is 1 or 2, the future for that person is bright. That creature can choose to gain advantage on any one d20 roll within 24 hours. If the result is 3 or 4, the future for that person is bad. The dm will inflict disadvantage on a d20 roll of their choice that the creature makes within 24 hours.</p>",
